<subSubSection id="EC9A6526DD5BFFBBFF4033E3FDCFD3B9" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="A43F36ADDD5BFFBBFF4033E3FDCFD3B9" blockId="9.[151,1436,1481,1686]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">
<emphasis id="96F4EABFDD5BFFBBFF4033E3FEF0D0CD" bold="true" box="[199,315,1481,1506]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="63804D2EDD5BFFBBFE4433E3FDF8D0CD" authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1882" box="[451,563,1481,1506]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Acanthochitonidae" genus="Leptoplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="96F4EABFDD5BFFBBFE4433E3FDF8D0CD" box="[451,563,1481,1506]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Leptoplax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had been considered to represent a synonym of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="63804D2EDD5BFFBBFB5D33E3FA8AD0CD" authorityName="H. Adams" authorityYear="1861" box="[1242,1345,1481,1506]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Acanthochitonidae" genus="Notoplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="96F4EABFDD5BFFBBFB5D33E3FA8AD0CD" box="[1242,1345,1481,1506]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Notoplax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but has been reinstated by 
<bibRefCitation id="C0114B5CDD5BFFBBFEEA33C7FDB1D329" author="Gowlett-Holmes" box="[365,634,1517,1542]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" refString="Gowlett-Holmes, K. L. (2001) Polyplacophora. In: Wells, A. &amp; Houston, W. W. K. (Eds.), Zoological Catalogue of Australia. Fol. 17.2. Mollusca: Aplacophora, Polyplacophora, Scaphopoda, Cephalopoda. CSIRO Publishing, Melbourne, pp. 19 - 84." type="book chapter" year="2001">Gowlett-Holmes (2001)</bibRefCitation>
after redefinition of the latter genus (
<bibRefCitation id="C0114B5CDD5BFFBBFBA233C7FAEED329" author="Gowlett-Holmes" box="[1061,1317,1517,1542]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" refString="Gowlett-Holmes, K. L. (1991) Redefinition of the genus Notoplax H. Adams, 1861, and recognition of the monotypic New Zealand genus Pseudotonicia Ashby, 1928 (Mollusca: Polyplacophora: Acanthochitonidae). Journal of the Malacological Society of Australia, 12, 77 - 88." type="journal article" year="1991">Gowlett-Holmes 1991</bibRefCitation>
), although the redefinition of 
<taxonomicName id="63804D2EDD5BFFBBFEE9303BFE15D305" authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1882" box="[366,478,1553,1578]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Acanthochitonidae" genus="Leptoplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="96F4EABFDD5BFFBBFEE9303BFE15D305" box="[366,478,1553,1578]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Leptoplax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has not been given to date. Here we propose a new definition. The main criteria to distinguish the two genera are the morphology of the sutural laminae of the tail valve and the radula, especially of the central and the first lateral teeth. However, further research including molecular analysis is needed to establish better definition for both genera.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
